               <p>JOHN BULLOCK. I am an <rs id="t18280911-238-viclabel1219" type="occupation">ironmonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-238-victim1347 t18280911-238-viclabel1219"></join>, and live in Featherstone-street, City-road. On the 26th of July, I was out; I had seen this kettle before nine o'clock that morning, and I saw it again at the office - it has my privatemark in it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-238-person1348">
                  HENRY 
                  WILLIAM TREVIS
               <interp inst="t18280911-238-person1348" type="surname" value="WILLIAM TREVIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-238-person1348" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-238-person1348" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am apprentice to a ropemaker in Featherstone-street. On the 26th of July, I was looking out at a window up stairs, and saw the prisoner looking into the prosecutor's window - he then took the kettle, and walked up the street with it; there was another person with him - I told a man who worked in the room with me; I went down and pursued him, and took him in the City-road with the kettle - I lost sight of him for about five minutes, but I am sure he is the same person.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-238-person1349">
                  GEORGE 
                  WOODGATE
               <interp inst="t18280911-238-person1349" type="surname" value="WOODGATE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-238-person1349" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-238-person1349" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I received the prisoner.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was going to my dinner, and saw a lad turn the corner of Featherstone-street, and put down the kettle at a door - I took it up.</p>
               <p>
